---
import ChapterHead from "../ChapterHead.astro";
import ConclusionBox from "../ConclusionBox.astro";
---

<div
  id="prototype-ipad-figma"
  class="chapter h-full visible-page-width-disabled relative"
>
  <ChapterHead title="Tablet: Figma." bottom={true} height={120}>
    <p>
      We developed a Figma prototype that we would be able to test with our
      secondary Target Audience, people in the streets, willing to record a
      message.
    </p>
    <span
      >(The figma prototype is available <a
        href="https://www.figma.com/proto/z3IIqtgjieYcYNmWIfcN3a/UX4?page-id=75%3A294&type=design&node-id=182-216&viewport=737%2C-96%2C0.18&t=REkqHWYmSTAR6rsT-1&scaling=min-zoom&starting-point-node-id=182%3A216&show-proto-sidebar=1&mode=design"
        >here</a
      >.)</span
    >
  </ChapterHead>

  <div class="test absolute left-[500px] top-0">
    <div>
      <span class="test-col-title">Testing: Pre-Build</span>
      <div class="test-col green parallax-plane-1-prototype-ipad-figma">
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">Who are our Target User?</span>
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Random people walking in the center.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">What are we testing?</span>
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>People saying things in the microphone.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>People navigating the iPad.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">What is the user goal?</span>
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>To record an improvised message.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">What materials do we need?</span>
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Phone for calling.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Phone for recording.</span>
            </li>

            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Instructions.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Flowerbed.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <span class="test-col-title">Testing: Pre-Test</span>
      <div class="test-col orange">
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">What is the scenario?</span>
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span
                >Random person walks through the city and feels like making
                someones day.</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">What CAN'T we tell the user before testing?</span
          >
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Explain what to do.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Give them inspiration about what to say.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q"
            >What do we need to tell the user before testing?</span
          >
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>A short description of the project.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Permissions to be filmed and recorded.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Imagine there is a flowerbed.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>They can read the instructions on the screen.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q">What are the user tasks?</span>
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>1. Read the instructions.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>2. Record the message, following the instructions.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>3. Navigate an inspiration.</span>
            </li>

            <li class="test-line">
              <span>4. play/pause the recording.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="test-s">
          <span class="test-q"
            >What questions do we need to ask the user afterwards?</span
          >
          <ul class="test-a">
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Would you do this in a real life scenario?</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span
                >Would you like this if you would be lonely/stuck at home?</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span
                >Would this setup make you stop and read the instructions?</span
              >
            </li>

            <li class="test-line">
              <span>How do you feel after having send a message?</span>
            </li>
            <li class="test-line">
              <span>Flowerbed.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <span class="test-col-title">Testing: Test</span>
      <div class="test-grid">
        <div
          class="h-[60px] border-b-[1px] border-grey flex justify-center items-center bg-white sticky top-0"
        >
          User Task ID
        </div>
        <div
          class="h-[60px] border-b-[1px] border-grey flex justify-center items-center bg-white sticky top-0"
        >
          User ID
        </div>
        <div
          class="h-[60px] border-b-[1px] border-grey flex justify-center items-center bg-white sticky top-0"
        >
          What are they saying?
        </div>
        <div
          class="h-[60px] border-b-[1px] border-grey flex justify-center items-center bg-white sticky top-0"
        >
          Notes
        </div>
        <div
          class="h-[60px] border-b-[1px] border-grey flex justify-center items-center bg-white sticky top-0"
        >
          Score
        </div>
        <span>1</span>
        <span>1</span>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Explanation seems to be clear.</span>
        <span>4/5</span>

        <span>2</span>
        <span>1</span>
        <span>“So now, I just record something?”</span>
        <span>They asked us for explanation, so it’s not completely clear.</span
        >
        <span>2/5</span>

        <span>3</span>
