          didn't seem clear.</span
        >
        <span>0/5</span>

        <span>1</span>
        <span>5</span>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Instructions seemed clear enough.</span>
        <span>3/5</span>

        <span>2</span>
        <span>5</span>
        <span>“Do i press here?”</span>
        <span>Had to look for the right button. Hesistant to use the iPad.</span
        >
        <span>2/5</span>

        <span>3</span>
        <span>5</span>
        <span>"hallo? Hallo??"</span>
        <span>They seemed confused about no one being on the other side.</span>
        <span>3/5</span>

        <span>4</span>
        <span>5</span>
        <span>“So no one is going to answer me?”</span>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>3/5</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative">
      <span class="test-col-title">Testing: Post-Test</span>
      <div class="absolute top-[10%]">
        <ConclusionBox chapter="prototype-lights" id={0} black={false}>
          <span
            >People did show a lot of satisfaction after having said something.
            A lot of people commented on the fact that we need to take care of
            each other.
          </span>
        </ConclusionBox>
      </div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-[40%]">
        <ConclusionBox chapter="prototype-lights" id={0} black={true}>
          <span
            >We realised that a lot of young people were actually interested in
            having a flower at home. They seem to like the social aspect more
            and some said that they could use the contact with the city.
          </span>
        </ConclusionBox>
      </div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-[10%]">
        <ConclusionBox chapter="prototype-lights" id={0} black={true}>
          <span
            >There was still a lot of confusing when using the iPad. Sometimes
            the confusion was about the testing part of it, where it might be
            more clear what they're supposed to do if the project was actually
            realised. Other people were confused after reading the explanation.
          </span>
        </ConclusionBox>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    #prototype-ipad-figma {
      @apply min-w-[5500px];
    }
  </style>
</div>
